cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.SD

This paper is about natural language generation (NLG) in task-oriented dialogue systems, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also proposes a meta-learning approach for NLG, which involves optimizing the model to adapt to new low-resource NLG tasks, which is related to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of neural networks for NLG also suggests a connection to neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). Finally, the paper evaluates its approach on a large multi-domain dataset, which involves data management and analysis (cs.SD).
